            <abstract>
                <p><term key="Magic">Magic prayer</term> against the harm of <term key="demon">Zār</term> and 
                    <term key="demon">Tǝgridā</term> containing a sequence of Arabic or Islamic names or terms
                    used as <term key="Asmat">ʾasmāt</term>, e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ar">ʾalāhumā</foreign> 
                    (cf. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Griaule1930recettes"/><citedRange unit="page">111, 113</citedRange>
                    <citedRange unit="item">CXVIII</citedRange></bibl>).
                    The beginning of the prayer is <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ዛር፡ ወትግሪዳ፡</foreign>, which is similar to the
                    recurring phrase in prayers in <ref type="mss" corresp="CamOr1885#ms_i52"/>
                    (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ዛር፡ ወትግሪዳ፡</foreign> and 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">እምሕማመ፡ ዛር፡ ወትግሪዳ፡</foreign>.</p>
            </abstract>
